	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table6">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1154">Rivervale</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Halfling Cleric Newbie Armor</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Halfling Cleric Newbie Armor</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=579569"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Clud</a> | 
		                        6/26/2002 7:15:13 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">This is the new quest for relatively new Halfling Clerics to get magical armor. <BR>
All pieces of armor except the Breast plate are AC 4-5 and buff wis and agi +1-+3<BR>
the Breastplate is AC12 wis+3 agi+5.<BR>
You need to talk to the trainer standing outside the door to the clerics guild in RV in order to get each recipe and each enchanted mold. You also get a container in which to combine the bits that you will collect into a sheet of enchanted metal. Combine this sheet and the appropriate enchanted mold in a forge to create the piece. The combining does NOT seem to be failable.<BR>
<BR>
All bits can either be bought in Rivervale or drop off of critters in Misty Thicket. <BR>
ALL ARMOR IS NO DROP AND ONLY THE BRACERS ARE NOT LORE.<BR>
You need:<BR>
Bricks of Crude Iron ore for each piece (I'll just say Bricks from now on). These drop off of Goblin Warriors in MT, but lots of other critters in other zones drop them, and merchants will often have 1 or 2 for sale for 5-6 sp, so young characters can still complete some of these quests.<BR>
<BR>
Bracers (not lore so you can make two)-2 Bricks Bixie Stinger(Any Bixie), Runny Eye Warbead(Goblin Warriors)<BR>
<BR>
Boots- 2 Bricks, 2 Dark Elf Skins(Shadowed Assasins-No Drop), 2 Bixie Wings (any Bixie), Rat Foot (any rat)<BR>
<BR>
Arm Guards- 3 Bricks, 1 Giant Wood Spider Hairs (Giant Wood Spider-No Drop),2 Thorn Drakeling Scales (Good luck a) finding a Thorn Drakeling, b) getting it to drop ANYTHING, these are tradeable however), 2 Lettuce (all veggies buyable from fruitstand outside druid guild)<BR>
<BR>
Greaves-4 Bricks 2 Large Yellow Jacket Tergites (from Large Yellow Jackets-No Drop, seem to be a quite rare drop, but needed for other class quests too!), 2 Death Fist Slashed Belts(Orc Centurions and higher-tradeable, but you prob. knew that. Frequently can be bought from merchies too.)-----I'm still working on this one as I've only gotten 1 LYJ tergite to drop on Vazaelle.<BR>
<BR>
Gauntlets-3 Bricks, 1 Dark Elf Skin(see above), 2 Bone Chips (NOTE MT only has 1 decaying that spawns in it on the goblin side of the wall, but plenty of &quot;grown up&quot; skeletons at the rat ruins), 1 Vegetables (Fruit Stall outside druid guild)<BR>
<BR>
Breastplate-5 bricks, 1 Death Fist Slashed Belt(see above), 1 Giant Yellow Jacket Sternite(Drops off of Giant Yellow Jackets curiously enough, its NO DROP and can be infuriatingly inconsistently dropped - i.e. none for a day or two and then several in a couple of hours), 2 Dark Elf Skins, 1 UNDAMAGED MOSSY RAT PELT (exactly that, not just a mossy rat pelt. This is tradeable and a rare drop from diseased rats).<BR>
<BR>
There is a capping part of this quest that I haven't complete yet, you need 3 pristine stingers (Giant Yellow Jackets, no drop) and the Research Annals that are supposed to drop off of a Muddite Recordkeeper (I think this must be a relatively new monster added for this quest, but I haven't hunted the gorge). If this follows other quests, this will give you some magic weapon with stats better than a regular weapon of its type, but hardly anything to write home about.<BR>
<BR>
This quest is LONG, at least lately. I complete the Freeport Warriors quest in 6 hours or so. This quest has taken me 24+ hours and 11 levels, and I still havent finished it(need the pants...so if you see a halfling running around with all kinds of crazy armor on, but no pants, you know why). The undamaged mossy rat pelt alone took 6 hours of camping diseased rats. WELL over 100 diseased rats fell beneath my weapon of the moment before one finally dropped. I collected about 50 Ruined mossy rat pelts and 4 or 5 mossy rat pelts in the same time.<BR>
<BR>
Thats not the hard part of this quest.<BR>
<BR>
The Thorn Drakelings are. In both cases, I ended up trading for the Scales. I've never actually dropped one. Of the less than 10 TDs that I've managed to find and then been lucky enough to get to them first to kill, I've seen just 3 Ruined scales(used by rangers and warriors I think). Most of the other halfling noob armor quests are on the same level time wise. This all on Vazaelle.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The result is most of the Shouts and OOCs in MT are &quot;PLEASE SHOUT IF YOU DROP XXXXXX&quot; or &quot;XXXXXX DROPPED AT LOC XXXXX YYYYYY&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
I did make a lot of friends doing this quest. I strongly feel that its best to work with everyone else to achieve these quests rather than trying to go the route of dropping cash to your alt and buying it. The stuff is just too darn rarely dropped to worry about buying. If you have cash, there are certainly better things to spend it on than hanging out in the thicket waiting for some stupid bit to drop so you can spend it and hoping you can get to the spot in time to loot.<BR>
<BR>
Unless there just happened to be spawn/drop issues when I was doing this quest(which came a couple of days after a major reboot and downtime, and spawns and drops always seem nerfed after that), you will green or light blue most cons you need to kill before this is over, so there comes a point where you ask yourself &quot;Why?&quot; and decide to move on.<BR>
<BR>
Poppazin&lt;Shadows of Reality&gt;<BR>
Cleric of the 11th Burrow<BR>
Vazaelle<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

